{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I became an inventor by accident. \n"},{"time":2000,"text":"I was out of the air force in 1956. No, no, that's not true: \n"},{"time":7000,"text":"I went in in 1956, came out in 1959, \n"},{"time":10000,"text":"was working at the University of Washington, \n"},{"time":12000,"text":"and I came up with an idea, from reading a magazine article, \n"},{"time":14000,"text":"for a new kind of a phonograph tone arm. \n"},{"time":17000,"text":"Now, that was before cassette tapes, C.D.s, DVDs --"},{"time":20000,"text":"any of the cool stuff we've got now. \n"},{"time":22000,"text":"And it was an arm that, \n\n"},{"time":24000,"text":"instead of hinging and pivoting as it went across the record, \n"},{"time":28000,"text":"went straight: a radial, linear tracking tone arm. \n"},{"time":32000,"text":"And it was the hardest invention I ever made, but it got me started,\n"},{"time":36000,"text":"and I got really lucky after that. \n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"And without giving you too much of a tirade, \n"},{"time":40000,"text":"I want to talk to you about an invention I brought with me today: \n"},{"time":43000,"text":"my 44th invention. No, that's not true either. \n"},{"time":47000,"text":"Golly, I'm just totally losing it. \n"},{"time":49000,"text":"My 44th patent; about the 15th invention. \n"},{"time":52000,"text":"I call this hypersonic sound. \n"},{"time":55000,"text":"I'm going to play it for you in a couple minutes, \n"},{"time":57000,"text":"but I want to make an analogy before I do\n"},{"time":59000,"text":"to this."},{"time":62000,"text":"I usually show this hypersonic sound and people will say, \n"},{"time":65000,"text":"That's really cool, but what's it good for? \n"},{"time":68000,"text":"And I say, What is the light bulb good for? \n"},{"time":71000,"text":"Sound, light: I'm going to draw the analogy. \n"},{"time":74000,"text":"When Edison invented the light bulb, pretty much looked like this.\n"},{"time":77000,"text":"Hasn't changed that much. \n"},{"time":79000,"text":"Light came out of it in every direction. \n"},{"time":82000,"text":"Before the light bulb was invented, \n"},{"time":84000,"text":"people had figured out how to put a reflector behind it, \n"},{"time":87000,"text":"focus it a little bit; \n"},{"time":89000,"text":"put lenses in front of it,\n"},{"time":91000,"text":"focus it a little bit better."},{"time":93000,"text":"Ultimately we figured out how to make things like lasers \n"},{"time":96000,"text":"that were totally focused. \n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"Now, think about where the world would be today \n"},{"time":101000,"text":"if we had the light bulb,"},{"time":105000,"text":"but you couldn't focus light;"},{"time":107000,"text":"if when you turned one on it just went wherever it wanted to."},{"time":112000,"text":"That's the way loudspeakers pretty much are."},{"time":115000,"text":"You turn on the loudspeaker,"},{"time":117000,"text":"and after almost 80 years of having those gadgets,"},{"time":120000,"text":"the sound just kind of goes where it wants."},{"time":123000,"text":"Even when you're standing in front of a megaphone,"},{"time":125000,"text":"it's pretty much every direction."},{"time":127000,"text":"A little bit of differential, but not much."},{"time":130000,"text":"If the light bulb was the way the speaker is,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and you couldn't focus or sharpen the edges or define it,"},{"time":136000,"text":"we wouldn't have that, or movies in general,"},{"time":141000,"text":"or computers, or T.V. sets,"},{"time":144000,"text":"or C.D.s, or DVDs -- and just go down the list"},{"time":147000,"text":"of what the importance is \n"},{"time":149000,"text":"of being able to focus light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"Now, after almost 80 years of having sound,"},{"time":156000,"text":"I thought it was about time that we figure out"},{"time":158000,"text":"a way to put sound where you want to."},{"time":162000,"text":"I have a couple of units."},{"time":164000,"text":"That guy there was made for a demo I did yesterday early in the day"},{"time":166000,"text":"for a big car maker in Detroit who wants to put them in a car --"},{"time":169000,"text":"small version, over your head --"},{"time":171000,"text":"so that you can actually get binaural sound in a car."},{"time":175000,"text":"What if I could aim sound the way I aim light?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180000,"text":"I got this waterfall I recorded in my back yard."},{"time":183000,"text":"Now, you're not going to hear a thing unless it hits you."},{"time":187000,"text":"Maybe if I hit the side wall it will bounce around the room."},{"time":190000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":193000,"text":"The sound is being made right next to your ears. Is that cool?"},{"time":197000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":205000,"text":"Because I have some limited time, I'll cut it off for a second,"},{"time":207000,"text":"and tell you about how it works and what it's good for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"Course, like light, it's great to be able to put sound"},{"time":213000,"text":"to highlight a clothing rack, or the cornflakes, or the toothpaste,"},{"time":216000,"text":"or a talking plaque in a movie theater lobby."},{"time":219000,"text":"Sony's got an idea -- Sony's our biggest customers right now."},{"time":223000,"text":"They tried this back in the '60s"},{"time":225000,"text":"and were too smart, and so they gave up."},{"time":227000,"text":"But they want to use it -- seriously."},{"time":230000,"text":"There's a mix an inventor has to have."},{"time":232000,"text":"You have to be kind of smart,"},{"time":234000,"text":"and though I did not graduate from college doesn't mean I'm stupid,"},{"time":238000,"text":"because you cannot be stupid and do very much in the world today."},{"time":241000,"text":"Too many other smart people out there. So."},{"time":243000,"text":"I just happened to get my education in a little different way."},{"time":245000,"text":"I'm not at all against education."},{"time":248000,"text":"I think it's wonderful; I think sometimes people,"},{"time":250000,"text":"when they get educated, lose it:"},{"time":253000,"text":"they get so smart they're unwilling to look at things that they know better than."},{"time":257000,"text":"And we're living in a great time right now,"},{"time":260000,"text":"because almost everything's being explored anew."},{"time":263000,"text":"I have this little slogan that I use a lot, which is:"},{"time":266000,"text":"virtually nothing --"},{"time":268000,"text":"and I mean this honestly --"},{"time":270000,"text":"has been invented yet."},{"time":272000,"text":"We're just starting."},{"time":274000,"text":"We're just starting to really discover the laws of nature and science and physics."},{"time":278000,"text":"And this is, I hope, a little piece of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"Sony's got this vision back -- to get myself on track --"},{"time":284000,"text":"that when you stand in the checkout line in the supermarket,"},{"time":287000,"text":"you're going to watch a new T.V. channel."},{"time":289000,"text":"They know that when you watch T.V. at home,"},{"time":291000,"text":"because there are so many choices"},{"time":293000,"text":"you can change channels, miss their commercials."},{"time":297000,"text":"A hundred and fifty-one million people every day stand in the line at the supermarket."},{"time":302000,"text":"Now, they've tried this a couple years ago and it failed,"},{"time":304000,"text":"because the checker gets tired of hearing the same message"},{"time":306000,"text":"every 20 minutes, and reaches out, turns off the sound."},{"time":310000,"text":"And, you know, if the sound isn't there, the sale typically isn't made."},{"time":313000,"text":"For instance, like, when you're on an airplane, they show the movie,"},{"time":316000,"text":"you get to watch it for free;"},{"time":318000,"text":"when you want to hear the sound, you pay."},{"time":320000,"text":"And so ABC and Sony have devised this new thing"},{"time":324000,"text":"where when you step in the line in the supermarket --"},{"time":327000,"text":"initially it'll be Safeways. It is Safeways;"},{"time":330000,"text":"they're trying this in three parts of the country right now --"},{"time":332000,"text":"you'll be watching TV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"And hopefully they'll be sensitive"},{"time":336000,"text":"that they don't want to offend you with just one more outlet."},{"time":338000,"text":"But what's great about it, from the tests that have been done, is,"},{"time":341000,"text":"if you don't want to hear it,"},{"time":343000,"text":"you take about one step to the side and you don't hear it."},{"time":346000,"text":"So, we create silence as much as we create sound."},{"time":350000,"text":"ATMs that talk to you; nobody else hears it."},{"time":353000,"text":"Sit in bed, two in the morning, watch TV;"},{"time":355000,"text":"your spouse, or someone, is next to you, asleep;"},{"time":359000,"text":"doesn't hear it, doesn't wake up."},{"time":361000,"text":"We're also working on noise canceling things like snoring, noise from automobiles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"I have been really lucky with this technology:"},{"time":371000,"text":"all of a sudden as it is ready, the world is ready to accept it."},{"time":376000,"text":"They have literally beat a path to our door."},{"time":378000,"text":"We've been selling it since about last September, October,"},{"time":381000,"text":"and it's been immensely gratifying."},{"time":384000,"text":"If you're interested in what it costs -- I'm not selling them today --"},{"time":386000,"text":"but this unit, with the electronics and everything,"},{"time":388000,"text":"if you buy one, is around a thousand bucks."},{"time":390000,"text":"We expect by this time next year,"},{"time":392000,"text":"it'll be hundreds, a few hundred bucks, to buy it."},{"time":394000,"text":"It's not any more pricey than regular electronics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398000,"text":"Now, when I played it for you, you didn't hear the thunderous bass."},{"time":402000,"text":"This unit that I played goes from about 200 hertz to above the range of hearing."},{"time":407000,"text":"It's actually emitting ultrasound -- low-level ultrasound --"},{"time":411000,"text":"that's about 100,000 vibrations per second."},{"time":414000,"text":"And the sound that you're hearing,"},{"time":416000,"text":"unlike a regular speaker on which all the sound is made on the face,"},{"time":420000,"text":"is made out in front of it, in the air."},{"time":423000,"text":"The air is not linear, as we've always been taught."},{"time":427000,"text":"You turn up the volume just a little bit --"},{"time":429000,"text":"I'm talking about a little over 80 decibels --"},{"time":432000,"text":"and all of a sudden the air begins to corrupt signals you propagate."},{"time":436000,"text":"Here's why: the speed of sound is not a constant. It's fairly slow."},{"time":441000,"text":"It changes with temperature and with barometric pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445000,"text":"Now, imagine, if you will, without getting too technical,"},{"time":448000,"text":"I'm making a little sine wave here in the air."},{"time":451000,"text":"Well, if I turn up the amplitude too much,"},{"time":454000,"text":"I'm having an effect on the pressure,"},{"time":457000,"text":"which means during the making of that sine wave,"},{"time":460000,"text":"the speed at which it is propagating is shifting."},{"time":463000,"text":"All of audio as we know it"},{"time":466000,"text":"is an attempt to be more and more perfectly linear."},{"time":470000,"text":"Linearity means higher quality sound."},{"time":474000,"text":"Hypersonic sound is exactly the opposite:"},{"time":478000,"text":"it's 100 percent based on non-linearity."},{"time":482000,"text":"An effect happens in the air, it's a corrupting effect of the sound --"},{"time":487000,"text":"the ultrasound in this case -- that's emitted,"},{"time":490000,"text":"but it's so predictable"},{"time":492000,"text":"that you can produce very precise audio out of that effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"Now, the question is, where's the sound made?"},{"time":499000,"text":"Instead of being made on the face of the cone,"},{"time":501000,"text":"it's made at literally billions of little independent points"},{"time":505000,"text":"along this narrow column in the air,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and so when I aim it towards you,"},{"time":511000,"text":"what you hear is made right next to your ears."},{"time":514000,"text":"I said we can shorten the column,"},{"time":517000,"text":"we can spread it out to cover the couch."},{"time":519000,"text":"I can put it so that one ear hears one speaker,"},{"time":522000,"text":"the other ear hears the other. That's true binaural sound."},{"time":526000,"text":"When you listen to stereo on your home system,"},{"time":529000,"text":"your both ears hear both speakers."},{"time":532000,"text":"Turn on the left speaker sometime"},{"time":534000,"text":"and notice you're hearing it also in your right ear."},{"time":536000,"text":"So, the stage is more restricted --"},{"time":539000,"text":"the sound stage that's supposed to spread out in front of you."},{"time":542000,"text":"Because the sound is made in the air along this column,"},{"time":545000,"text":"it does not follow the inverse square law,"},{"time":547000,"text":"which says it drops off about two thirds"},{"time":550000,"text":"every time you double the distance:"},{"time":552000,"text":"6dB every time you go from one meter, for instance, to two meters."},{"time":557000,"text":"That means you go to a rock concert or a symphony,"},{"time":560000,"text":"and the guy in the front row gets the same level"},{"time":562000,"text":"as the guy in the back row, now, all of a sudden."},{"time":564000,"text":"Isn't that terrific?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"So, we've been, as I say, very successful, very lucky,"},{"time":570000,"text":"in having companies catch the vision of this,"},{"time":573000,"text":"from cars -- car makers who want to put a stereo system in the front for the kids,"},{"time":577000,"text":"and a separate system in the back --"},{"time":579000,"text":"oh, no, the kids aren't driving today."},{"time":581000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":582000,"text":"I was seeing if you were listening."},{"time":584000,"text":"Actually, I haven't had breakfast yet."},{"time":586000,"text":"A stereo system in the front for mom and dad,"},{"time":590000,"text":"and maybe there's a little DVD player in the back for the kids,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and the parents don't want to be bothered with that,"},{"time":595000,"text":"or their rap music or whatever."},{"time":597000,"text":"So, again, this idea of being able to put sound anywhere you want to"},{"time":600000,"text":"is really starting to catch on."},{"time":602000,"text":"It also works for transmitting and communicating data."},{"time":606000,"text":"It also works five times better underwater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"We've got the military -- have just deployed some of these into Iraq,"},{"time":613000,"text":"where you can put fake troop movements"},{"time":616000,"text":"quarter of a mile away on a hillside."},{"time":618000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":621000,"text":"Or you can whisper in the ear of a supposed terrorist some Biblical verse."},{"time":625000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":627000,"text":"I'm serious. And they have these infrared devices"},{"time":633000,"text":"that can look at their countenance,"},{"time":636000,"text":"and see a fraction of a degree Kelvin in temperature shift"},{"time":640000,"text":"from 100 yards away when they play this thing."},{"time":643000,"text":"And so, another way of hopefully determining who's friendly and who isn't."},{"time":647000,"text":"We make a version with this which puts out 155 decibels."},{"time":652000,"text":"Pain is 120."},{"time":654000,"text":"So it allows you to go nearly a mile away and communicate with people,"},{"time":658000,"text":"and there can be a public beach just off to the side,"},{"time":660000,"text":"and they don't even know it's turned on."},{"time":662000,"text":"We sell those to the military presently for about 70,000 dollars,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and they're buying them as fast as we can make them."},{"time":668000,"text":"We put it on a turret with a camera, so that when they shoot at you,"},{"time":673000,"text":"you're over there, and it's there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"I have a bunch of other inventions."},{"time":678000,"text":"I invented a plasma antenna, to shift gears."},{"time":680000,"text":"Looked up at the ceiling of my office one day --"},{"time":683000,"text":"I was working on a ground-penetrating radar project --"},{"time":687000,"text":"and my physicist CEO came in and said, \"We have a real problem."},{"time":691000,"text":"We're using very short wavelengths."},{"time":694000,"text":"We've got a problem with the antenna ringing."},{"time":696000,"text":"When you run very short wavelengths,"},{"time":698000,"text":"like a tuning fork the antenna resonates,"},{"time":700000,"text":"and there's more energy coming out of the antenna"},{"time":702000,"text":"than there is the backscatter from the ground"},{"time":704000,"text":"that we're trying to analyze, taking too much processing.\""},{"time":707000,"text":"I says, \"Why don't we make an antenna that only exists when you want it?"},{"time":712000,"text":"Turn it on; turn it off."},{"time":715000,"text":"That's a fluorescent tube refined.\""},{"time":720000,"text":"I just sold that for a million and a half dollars, cash."},{"time":723000,"text":"I took it back to the Pentagon after it got declassified,"},{"time":726000,"text":"when the patent issued, and told the people back there about it,"},{"time":730000,"text":"and they laughed, and then I took them back a demo and they bought."},{"time":732000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"Any of you ever wore a Jabber headphone -- the little cell headphones?"},{"time":739000,"text":"That's my invention. I sold that for seven million dollars."},{"time":741000,"text":"Big mistake: it just sold for 80 million dollars two years ago."},{"time":745000,"text":"I actually drew that up on a little crummy Mac computer"},{"time":748000,"text":"in my attic at my house,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and one of the many designs which they have now"},{"time":754000,"text":"is still the same design I drew way back when."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"So, I've been really lucky as an inventor."},{"time":759000,"text":"I'm the happiest guy you're ever going to meet."},{"time":763000,"text":"And my dad died before he realized anybody in the family"},{"time":768000,"text":"would maybe, hopefully, make something out of themselves."},{"time":771000,"text":"You've been a great audience. I know I've jumped all over the place."},{"time":773000,"text":"I usually figure out what my talk is when I get up in front of a group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776000,"text":"Let me give you, in the last minute,"},{"time":778000,"text":"one more quick demo of this guy,"},{"time":781000,"text":"for those of you that haven't heard it."},{"time":784000,"text":"Can never tell if it's on."},{"time":786000,"text":"If you haven't heard it, raise your hand."},{"time":791000,"text":"Getting it over there?"},{"time":794000,"text":"Get the cameraman."},{"time":797000,"text":"Yeah, there you go."},{"time":799000,"text":"I've got a Coke can opening that's right in your head; that's really cool."},{"time":802000,"text":"Thank you once again."},{"time":804000,"text":"Appreciate it very much."}]}]}